@page "/flu-education/prevention"
@inject NavigationManager Navigation
<div class="content-container">
    <div class="header-section">
        <img src="/images/protection.png" alt="Prevention Icon" class="flu-icon" />
        <h1>Flu Prevention</h1>
    </div>
    <p>
        The best way to prevent flu is by getting vaccinated each year. Flu vaccines protect against the influenza viruses that research suggests will be most common during the upcoming season.
    </p>
    <p>
        In addition to getting vaccinated, you can take everyday precautions to stop the spread of germs:
    </p>
    <ul class="prevention-list">
        <li>Avoid close contact with sick people.</li>
        <li>If you are sick, limit contact with others as much as possible to keep from infecting them.</li>
        <li>Cover your nose and mouth with a tissue when you cough or sneeze.</li>
        <li>Wash your hands often with soap and water. If soap and water are not available, use an alcohol-based hand rub.</li>
        <li>Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth. Germs spread this way.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <button @onclick="GoToPreviousPage">Previous</button>
        <button @onclick="GoToNextPage">Next</button>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    /* Overall Page Background */
    body {
        background-color: #F0F8FF; /* Soft light blue background */
    }

    /* Content Container */
    .content-container {
        background-color: #FFFFFF; /* White background */
        padding: 40px; /* Increased padding */
        border-radius: 15px; /* Softer edges */
        box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); /* Stronger shadow */
        max-width: 1000px; /* Wider container */
        margin: 100px auto; /* More space above and below */
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
    }

    /* Header Section */
    .header-section {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center; /* Center content horizontally */
        margin-bottom: 30px; /* More space between header and paragraph */
    }

    .flu-icon {
        width: 80px; /* Larger icon */
        height: 80px;
        margin-right: 20px; /* Increased space between icon and title */
    }

    /* Title Styling */
    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem; /* Larger font size for main title */
        color: #333;
    }

    /* Paragraph Styling */
    p {
        font-size: 1.3rem; /* Increased font size */
        line-height: 1.8; /* More line height for better readability */
        color: #555;
        margin-bottom: 20px; /* Larger margin between paragraphs */
        text-align: center; /* Center-align text */
    }

    /* Prevention List Styling */
    .prevention-list {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: #555;
        padding-left: 20px;
        text-align: left; /* Align list items to the left */
    }

    .prevention-list li {
        margin-bottom: 10px; /* Space between list items */
    }
    /* Navigation Buttons */
    .navigation-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between; /* Align buttons to opposite sides */
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    button {
        font-size: 1rem;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 10px;
        color: #FFFFFF;
        background-color: #007ACC;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #005A99;
        }
</style>
@code {
    private void GoToPreviousPage()
    {
        Navigation.NavigateTo("/flu-education/causes"); // Change to the actual previous page path
    }

    private void GoToNextPage()
    {
        Navigation.NavigateTo("/flu-education/treatment"); // Change to the actual next page path
    }
}